      • isPrimitiveEntityType

        public static boolean isPrimitiveEntityType(java.lang.Class<?> type)
        A primitive entity type has the following requirements: 1. The hashCode() and equals() method must be deterministically implemented (and make sense with regard to the semantics of the type). 2. The toString() method should return the pre-processed string to be used as the primitive entity name during inference.

      • isScalarEntityType

        public boolean isScalarEntityType()
        Returns:
        true iff the type of this primitive entity is one for which comparison operations can be performed.

      • mapToRealValueConservingComparisonRelations

        public double mapToRealValueConservingComparisonRelations()
        For scalar entities only. For two scalar entities e1 and e2, suppose this method returns x1,x2 respectively. Then x1>x2 iff e1>e2. Note: For checking if two scalar entities are equal we use {@link PrimitiveEntity#equals(Object)} and not this method.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - if the type is not scalar.
